Soak 8-10 wooden skewers in a bowl of cold water for about 20 minutes.For the seasoning, combine all the seasoning ingredients together in a bowl. Add the meat and stir to coat in the spices, then thread the meat onto the skewers.Heat a dash of olive oil in a griddle pan until smoking and add the skewers, cooking for 2-3 minutes, or until browned on one side. Turn the skewers over and cook for a futher 1-2 minutes, or until browned and cooked to your liking, then transfer to a serving plate and serve immediately.